context: The School of English as a Second Language at George Brown College offers various English language programs in downtown Toronto. Some recommended programs include the English for Academic Purposes Program (R105), Pathway to Post-Secondary Certificate and Diploma program (R903), English as a Second Language Certificate Program (R901), English for Professional Success Certificate Program (R902), Occupation-Specific Language Training (OSLT) program, and English for Academic Purposes for International Students Program (R115). Interested applicants can apply to the part-time English as a Second Language certificate (R901) to improve personal, professional, and academic English language skills or the English for Professional Success program (R902) if they have advanced English skills. Additionally, there is a Continuing Education ESL Pathway to George Brown College Certificates and Diplomas (R903) to meet English Language admission requirements for George Brown certificate, diploma, or postgraduate certificate programs without co-op. Contacts for international recruitment representatives can be found on the website, and applicants can sign up for updates about application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and more. The phone number provided is 416-415-.
